Setting A Plymouth
1 Open Terminal Then Install plymouth By sudo pacman -S plymouth Run sudo nano /etc/default/grub Then Change GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="loglevel=3 quiet" to GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="quiet splash" Then Update grub using sudo grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg
2 If You Want Spinner Plymouth Theme Change watermark.png arch linux to Fallback Linux By sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/fallback-linux-logo.png /usr/share/plymouth/themes/spinner/watermark.png then sudo plymouth-set-default-theme spinner then sudo mkinitcpio -P
  Or If You Want BGRT (UEFI SYSTEMS ONLY) sudo plymouth-set-default-theme bgrt then sudo mkinitcpio -P
3 List Plymouth Themes On sudo plymouth-set-default-theme --list
4 Set Your Desired Theme By sudo plymouth-set-default-theme yourtheme Then sudo mkinitcpio -P
5 Reboot To Test

Customizing Plymouth

Breeze-text
1 Run sudo nano /usr/share/plymouth/themes/breeze-text/breeze-text.plymouth
2 If You See title=Arch Linux Change It To title=Fallback Linux
3 Rebuild initramfs
  sudo mkinitcpio -P

Fallback Linux Recommend To Use Tribar Theme Because Its Fallback Linux Default And Recommended Plymouth Theme
Set It Using sudo plymouth-set-default-theme tribar Then sudo mkinitcpio -P
